Narrative:
AT APPROXIMATELY 21:45 ON TUESDAY 2/20/18, GDLK 101 WITH 2 LOCOMOTIVES AND 57 CARS WAS TRAVELING NORTH ON THE GDLK MAIN. THE CREW WAS ENROUTE
TO HUGHART YARD IN GRAND RAPIDS WHEN THEY ENCOUNTERED A TRACK WASHOUT FROM HEAVY RAIN AND SNOW MELT AT MILEPOST 99.3 IN WYOMING, MICHIGAN. THE
ENGINEER WASUNABLE TO GET THE TRAIN STOPPED SHORT OF THE WASHOUT, CAUSING LOCOMOTIVES WAMX 4125 AND WAMX 4189 TODERAIL. WAMX 4125 TURNED
OVER ON ITS SIDE, WAMX 4189 WAS LEANING ONCE IT CAME TO REST. WAMX 4125 FUEL TANK WAS RUPTURED, ALLOWING DIESEL FUEL TO SPILL ONTO THE GROUND.

THIS ALLOWED THE ROADBED TO SUBSIDE AND THE TRACK AND THE WEST END OFTHE BRIDGE TO SINK. AS THE TRAIN TRAVERSED THIS SUNKEN AREA THE CREW BROUGHT THE TRAIN TO A STOP. NINE OF THE CARS IN THE TRAINS WERE LOADED COVERED HOPPERS, AND THE GATES USED TO UNLOAD THE PRODUCTWERE DAMAGED WHEN THE CARS PASSED OVER THE DEVIATION IN THE TRACK.

ON WEDNESDAY MAY 8TH AT 0800 THE SKOL 110 JOB WINFIELD SWITCH CREW CAME ON DUTY AND WENT TO THE WINFIELD YARD TO START THEIR DAY WHEN THEY NOTICED THAT THE WALNUT RIVER WAS STARTING TO RISE. THE CREWSTARTED PULLING TRACKS OUT OF THE YARD AND IN THE FIRST HOUR THAT THE TEAM WAS WORKING THE RIVER HADRISEN ABOUT 4 FEET AND WAS COMING INTO THE YARD. AS THE TEAM CONTINUED TO PULL TRACKS, THE RIVER WAS RISING AT ABOUT 3 TO 4 FEET AN HOUR. THE CITY OF WINFIELD INSTRUCTED THE 110 JOB TO GET OUT OF THEYARD BEFORE THEY INSTALLED THE GATES INTO THE LEVEE. AT 10 AM THE CREW LEFT THE YARD AND WAS ABLE TO GET 130 AND 3 COACH CARS OUT OF THE YARD. THEY HAD TO LEAVE 119 CARS BEHIND AS THE CITY OF WINFIELD DROPPED THE GATES INTO THE LEVEE. AFTER FLOOD SUBSIDED, A TOTAL OF 432 WHEEL SETS WERE FOUND TO BEDAMAGED AND WERE CHANGED OUT.

Narrative: THE YOZ60R-23 WAS PULLING DOWN THE BENICIA IND. LEAD (TRACK 700) WITH 4 LOCOMOTIVES AND 14 LOADED COVERED HOPPERS OF COKE FROM VALERO.  CREW WAS OPERATING LOCOMOTIVES IN RCL MODE WITH SPEED SELECTOR IN THE 10 MPH POSITION, WHEN THE CREW NOTICED THE MOVEMENT SLOWING DOWN AND THE TRAIN WENT INTO EMERGENCY AND CAME TO A STOP.  CREW WALKED BACK TO FIND THE 5TH HEAD CAR AND 8 ADDITIONAL CARS DERAILED.TRACK WAS FLOODED DUE TO A CITY WATER MAIN LEAK.
WHILE TRAVELLING EASTBOUND ON THE CALIENTE SUB, THE ZLADV-15, LEAD LOCOMOTIVE UP2766, ENCOUNTERED DEBRIS AND WATER ON TRACKS AND DERAILED FOUR LOCOMOTIVES AND ELEVEN CARS.

THE YSA81-05, HEADED INTO THE WEST END OF TRACK 8 AND CAME OUT THE EAST END TO MAKE A CUT ON THEIR SET OUT. CREW STOPPED TO MAKE A CUT AND WHEN THEY MADE A SEPARATION, TRAIN WENT INTO EMERGENCY. THE UTILITY PERSON WAS GETTING TO THE EAST END LEAD WHEN HE SAW THREE CARS WERE DERAILED. EAST YARD HAD SUBSTANTIAL RAIN FALL FOR TWO DAYS, CAUSING THE GROUND TO BE SATURATED WITH WATER AND ALLOWING THE TIES TO SINK INTO THE ROADBED.

HEAVY RAINS HAD BEEN ENCOUTERED AND WERE CONTINUOUS THROUGH OUT THE AREA FOR PAST 24 HOURS. THE TRAIN ENCOUNTERED AN AREA OF TRACK THAT THE ROADBED WAS COMPROMISED FROM THE FLOW OF WATER THAT WAS COMING OFF THE HILL AND DRAIING THROUGH A SMALL CULVERT NEARBY. THE T34507 WITH 2 LOCOMOTIVES AND 101 LOADED COAL CARS DERAILED LINES 12-25 AT CA 405.2
THE LRS54-10 WAS TRAVELLING NORTH ON THE FRESNO SUBDIVISION AT MP 56.2 WHEN 20 CARS HAD DERAILED DUETO A WASHOUT OF THE TRACK THAT OCCURRED UNDERNEATH THE TRAIN AS IT WAS TRAVERSING THE TRACK.
THE GSETTA-14 WAS TRAVERSING SOUTHBOUND NEAR MILEPOST 122 WHEN THEY ENCOUNTERED THE TRACK WASHED OUTDERAILING SEVERAL CARS.

TRAIN GSAN3E-24 WAS TRAVELING SOUTHBOUND ON MAIN TRACK AND WENT INTO UDE. CONDUCTOR WALKED THE TRAINAND FOUND DERAILED CARS. CREW WAS OPERATING IN A FLASH FLOOD AREA, ENCOUNTERED WATER OVER THE RAIL,TRAIN SUBSEQUENTLY WASHED OUT, DERAILING 11 CARS(ONE RE-RAILING ITSELF AT A GRADE CROSSING), 10 OTHERS DERAILING.

CCKSH9-03 EXPERIENCED A UDE.  AFTER TRYING UNSUCCESSFULLY TO REGAIN THEIR AIR, THEY DISCOVERED THAT14 CARS HAD DERAILED.  A REVIEW OF THE DOWNLOAD SHOWED THERE WERE NO HUMAN FACTOR ELEMENTS OR LOCOMOTIVE OPERATING DEFECTS THAT PLAYED A ROLE IN CONTRIBUTION OF THE DERAILMENT.  THE WEATHER IN OOSTBUGFROM 1300-1440 WAS HEAVY RAIN AND THUNDERSTORMS.  THE WEATHER IS THE ONLY CONSTANT FACTOR IN THIS DERAILMENT.  VIDEO OF THE ROADBED TAKEN AFTER THE INCIDENT SHOWS THAT THE ROADBED WAS SOFTENED DUE TOHEAVY RAIN.

H KCKBAR1 13 ON MAIN 1 TRACK DERAILED 9 RAILCARS DUE TO FLASH FLOODING AND RUNOFF WASHED OUT THE RAIL BRIDGE. NO HAZMAT RELEASED. CREW ON BOARD WERE 1 ENGINEER, 1 CONDUCTOR, AND 1 CONDUCTOR TRAINEE. DUE TO THE FLOODING WEATHER CONDTIONS THE CREW WENT OVERTIME.
A STANDING CUT OF 6 RAILCARS DERAILED IN YARD TRACK 7112 DUE TO AN EXTREME ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITION FLOOD.  NO HAZARDOUS MATERIALS WERE RELEASED.
U-RBSPEM4-28 DERAILED 3 RAILCARS WHILE TRAVERSING MAIN 1 TRACK DUE TO EXTREME ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITION, FLOOD. NO HAZARDOUS MATERIALS WERE RELEASED.
FLASH FLOOD BETWEEN MP 233 AND 247 ON POWDER RIVER SUB, THE CWINA-01 WAS STRANDED ON NO. 2 MAIN TRACK DUE TO WATER AND WASHOUTS.  THERE WAS NO DERAILMENT BUT 77 CARS AND DPU UP6637 HAD DAMAGE.
UNEXPECTED FLOODING AT EAST GULF MINE LED TO HIGH WATER OVER THE WHEELS OF CARS IN THE EAST GULF MINE.

ICE JAM ON THE CEDAR RIVER CAUSED FLOOD WATERS TO BACK UP INTO THE CEDAR RAPIDS YARD. 13 CARS ON TRACK CR06 AND 6 CARS ON TRACK CR23 WERE UNDER WATER REQUIRING WHEELS/BEARING TO BE CHANGED OUT. NO CARS WERE DERAILED AND NO DAMAGES TO TRACKS.
U-ZENFCL0-04 DERAILED 25 RAILCARS WHILE TRAVERSING MAIN 1 TRACK DUE TO EXTREME ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITION, FLOOD. NO HAZARDOUS MATERIALS WERE RELEASED.
FLASH FLOOD BETWEEN MP233 AND 247 ON POWDER RIVER SUB.  THE CPLNA-02 WAS STRANDED ON THE NO. 2 MAINTRACK DUE TO WASHOUTS.  THERE WAS NO DERAILMENT BUT 68 CARS AND DPU UP6915 SUFFERED DAMAGE.
MVPNP-22, LEAD LOCOMOTIVE UP7384, DERAILED 38 CARS AT MP 227.47 WHILE RUNNING AT 40 MPH ON THE WORTHINGTON SUB.  DERAILMENT DESTROYED THE BRIDGE AT THIS LOCATION OVER THE FLOYD RIVER.

Remote Control Locomotive: Remote control portable transmitter - more than one remote control transmitter
Contributing Accident Cause: Wide gage (due to defective or missing crossties)
Narrative: THE YTU22R-13 WAS PULLING CARS OUT OF THE RIP TRACK 510 WHEN THE REAR CAR CAME OFF THE RAIL.  THE POINT OF DERAILMENT SHOWS THAT THE RAIL SPREAD DUE TO WET SUBGRADE.  AS THE RAIL SPREAD, THE REAR TRUCK AND WHEELS RODE THE INSIDE OF THE RAIL UNTIL THE NORTH RAIL ROLLED OVER AND BOTH WHEELS HAD COME OFF THE RAIL.  IT APPEARS THAT DUE TO THE HEAVY RAINS AND FLOODING IN THE AREA THAT THE TRACK STRUCTURE GAVE OUT.  NO INJURIES WERE REPORTED.

L52481-04 WAS TRAVELING EAST ON SINGLE MAIN TRACK WHEN THEY CAME UPON A WASHOUT DUE TO HEAVY RAINS AND FLOODING IN THE AREA. THE ENGINEER PLACED THE TRAIN IN EMERGENCY. THE INCIDENT CAUSED DAMAGE TO THE LOCOMOTIVE'S FUEL TANK CAUSING APPROX. 500 GALLONS OF DIESEL FUEL TO LEAK. FOUR CARS WERE DERAILED: NRLX 400425, UP 94773, UP 94615 AND ADMX 63096. THE ENGINEER REPORTED AN INJURY TO HIS BACK.

THE Q46408 WAS OPERATING ON THE HAMLET SUBDIVISION TRAVELING NORTH FROM CAYCE SOUTH CAROLINA TO HAMLET NORTH CAROLINA.  THE TRAIN PASSED MP S 268.9 OPERATING AT 15MPH.  AS THE TRAIN AND CREW APPROACHED THE S 268.5 THE ROADBED AND BALLAST THAT SUPPORTED THE TRACK WERE NOT IN PLACE.  THE TRACK AND TIES WERE SUSPENDED WITH NO SUPPORTING MATERIAL FOR 100 FEET. THE LEAD ENGINE CSXT 535 TRAVERSED THE WASH OUT AND THE CSXT 247 DERAILED ALONG WITH THE HEAD FOUR CARS.

CREW ON THE RMDGPC-23, LEAD UNIT UP8742, REPORTED THAT THE LEAD LOCOMOTIVE WAS STOPPED ON TOP OF A WASHOUT LOCATION AND THE WATER WAS RISING.  CREW EVACUATED LOCOMOTIVE AND MOVED TO HIGHER GROUND WHERE THEY WERE RETRIEVED BY THE NAVARRO COUNTY WATER RESCUE TEAM.  CREW REPORTED 2 LOCOMOTIVES DERAILEDAND 45 CARS.  UP8337, EM SD70ACE, FUEL CAP = 4900 GALS, SPILLED 1092 GALS.

ZLAMQ-10 CREW HAD SWAPPED OUT WITH THE YMQ41 11 AT MESQUITE.  THE YMQ41 THEN PROCEEDED EAST IN THE PASS AT CPT 204.  THE CONDUCTOR WAS ON THE WEST END OF THE TRACK AND LINED THEM INTO TRACK 80.  THE CREW BEGAN TO SHOVE WEST WHEN THE EAST SET OF TRUCKS ON THE 1ST CAR FROM THE HEAD END (LOADED AUTORACK CP556411) DROPPED INSIDE THE RAIL.  FOLLOWING IT TO THE GROUND WITH REAR 3 AXLES WAS THE UP8127 THE 3RD LOCOMOTIVE IN THE CONSIST CAUSING THE TRAIN TO GO INTO EMERGENCY.  CAUSE OF THE DERAILMENT WASDETERMINED TO BE TRACK CAUSED.  AT THE POINT OF DERAILMENT, THE GAGE WAS MEASURED OVER 58 INCHES.
M53611 WAS PROCEEDING IN A NORTH DIRECTION WHEN WATER FLOW FROM AN ABUNDANCE OF RAIN, WASHED THE BRIDGE TIMBERS ALLOWING THE BRIDGE TO COLLAPSE INTO THE RIVER.

BPRR EMPLOYEES OBSERVING POTENTIAL FLOODING CONDITIONS IN CONNEQUESING CREEK THROUGHOUT THE NIGHT REPORTED THAT THE CREEK WAS COMING OUT OF THE BANKS. EQUIPMENT AND PARTS WERE BEING MOVED PRIOR TO PREVENT POTENTIAL FLOOD IMPACT BUT WATER ENTERED BPRR LOCOMOTIVE/CAR SHOP AND SUBMERGED THE WHEELS OF 24 CARS ON LEASED TRACK 13 IN CN YARD. 98 WHEELS WILL NEED TO BE CHANGED DUE TO WATER OVER THE BEARINGS.

THE ALDASB-29 WAS TRAVELING NORTH ON THE LOCKHART SUBDIVISION WHEN THE TRAIN ENCOUNTERED A WASHOUT AT APPROXIMATE MP 34.8, DERAILING THEIR LEAD UNIT AND TRAILING UNIT IN UPRIGHT POSITIONS AND THE HEAD11 CARS THAT WERE LOADED WITH AUTOS.

QSPNL-29 DERAILED THE LEAD SET OF TRUCKS ON THE DCLX7475, DUE TO BAD CROSS LEVEL ON THE MAIN TRACK WHICH WAS CAUSED BY A WASHOUT NEAR MP 66.52 ON THE LITTLE ROCK SUB IN MARSHALL.  THE CROSS LEVEL CAUSED THE REAR SET OF TRUCKS ON THE WEST SIDE OF THE TRACKS TO DIP AND RESULTED IN WHEEL LIFT ON THE FRONT SET OF TRUCKS, ALLOWING THE LEADING TRUCKS TO CLIMB THE HIGH SIDE OF THE CURVE ON THE EAST SIDEOF THE TRACK.  THE CREW OF THE QSPNL 29 HAD FELT A ROUGH SPOT IN THE TRACK AND STARTED WATCHING THETRAILING CARS.  THE CONDUCTOR NOTICED SPARKS FLYING UP FROM THE 10TH CAR AND THE TRAIN WAS BROUGHT TO A STOP.  UPON INSPECTION, THEY FOUND THE LEAD SET OF TRUCKS HAD DERAILED ON THE B END OF THE CAR WITH THE WHEELS ON THE WEST SIDE INSIDE THE TRACKS.
CREW ON THE ALDASB-28, LEAD UNIT UP5429 WENT OVER A WASHED OUT BRIDGE THAT GAVE WAY AND DERAILED 9 CARS.  NO INJURIES TO CREW.
JOB 204 WAS TRAVELING EASTBOUND WHEN THEY HIT A SINKHOLE AND DERAILED TWO LOCOMOTIVES AND SIX CARS.
BRIDGE FAILED IN MILAN, TN WITH CUT OF CARS ON BRIDGE DERAILING TWO CARS.
THE UEWKOT-18 HAD THE MAIN LINE WASH OUT FROM UNDERNEATH THE TRAIN ON THE CHEROKEE SUB AT MILEPOST 548.4, THUS DERAILING THREE CARS.
MPSPB-12 DERAILED THE LEADING LOCOMOTIVES AND 13 RAILCARS DUE TO WASH OUT.
